tip.text: I tried the Sakana Don, lunch special - $4.90. The fried fish really did made me think how long have they been reusing the oil. Miso soup too salty, fruit was a slice of canned pineapple.

So far... the hoshino spaghetti is a must have! Matcha souffle too. Servings are bigger than most pasta restaurants. Not enough manpower so the service is slow. Don't order icecream during peak hours.
Fluffy pancakes! In love with it. Totally didn't expect salted caramel and earl grey to be so good. The only problem is the noise level.
